RACE.FOOTNOTES: ALTERNATE REALITY broke out at the start, settled well off the pace under some urging, saved ground while ridden along on the turn, gained in the two path passing the five-sixteenths, rallied five wide into the stretch, took the advantage at the three-sixteenths while remaining on his inside lead under a left-handed crop, shook clear outside the furlong marker, switched to a right-handed crop while still on his inside lead outside the sixteenth-pole, continued on the left-lead to the wire and proved best under strong handling. MAJESTIC MICHAEL was hustled from the start, showed speed then chased the pace, went around the turn in the three path, took the lead inside the three-eighths, lost the advantage outside the quarter-pole, kept on well in pursuit of the leader in the stretch and earned the place. PHELPSY was bumped by an outside foe at the start then slow into stride, raced at the rear under urging, traveled around the turn in the two path, came five wide into the stretch under a left-handed crop while moving into contention, held a reasonable striking position under a strong drive into the final furlong and lacked the needed kick but finished willingly for the show. D HOPPER broke in and bumped with a foe, was forwardly placed on the outside, moved closer leaving the backstretch, issued a challenge in the four path on the turn, took the lead outside the quarter-pole, lost the advantage to the winner in upper stretch, dropped back into the final furlong and weakened. VENGE was a bit slow into stride, settled off the pace then dropped well back, went around the turn in the three path and was no factor. FINN'S MOMENT went to the front then moved clear with six furlongs to run, was challenged while in the two path early on the turn, lost the advantage inside the three-eighths pole, dropped back into the stretch and faded.

CANISY established the front and showed the way in hand along the inside, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, spun just off the inside into upper stretch, dug in under challenge rebuffing the threat of WONKA a furlong out confronted by the top one, dug in and was collared near the sixteenth pole, ran on to just hold on for the place honors. ARINA (GER) tracked the pace along the inside through the first turn and down the backstretch, tipped to the two path through the far turn coming under coaxing near the quarter pole, angled out three to four wide into upper stretch and offered up a mild kick to kick on belatedly to the finish just missing the place honors on the wire. BRAMBLE BAY coaxed from the gate, tracked the pace along the inside coming under coaxing with five-sixteenths to go, spun two to three wide into upper stretch, stayed on one paced to the finish. WONKA just off the inside in pursuit in closest aim of the leader, came under coaxing with five-sixteenths remaining, swung three wide into upper stretch and was heads apart for command briefly straightened away before being shaken off inside the eighth pole, then weakened in the late stages. TONED UP broke a beat slow without incident, saved ground at the tail of the field coming under coaxing three furlongs from home, continued in the inside route into upper stretch and trailed throughout.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPIKED raced in the three path around the first turn, was well placed just off the pace, came under strong urging late on the backstretch, raced inside to the two path for most of the far turn, shifted three wide late on that bend, rallied four wide into the stretch, chased outside the leader into the final furlong then made a bid and got up in the final sixteenth to narrowly prevail. KNOW IT ALL AUDREY went to the front, raced in the three path around the first turn, showed the way with a clear advantage, remained clear in the two to three path on the far turn, was asked for her best in upper stretch, led under a drive into the sixteenth, drifted out at that point and was caught while clear for the place. SUSPENDED CAMPAIGN traveled around the first turn in the three path, settled off the pace, was urged three wide around the far turn, gained under a drive in upper stretch and finished willingly to get the show. ANATOLIAN saved ground on the first turn, was urged along towards the rear, fell back leaving the backstretch, raced inside on the far turn, gained under a drive into upper stretch, held a reasonable striking position into the final furlong but lacked the needed response and flattened out. LIAM'S KISS raced inside to the two path on the first turn, was well placed down the backstretch, moved out while asked at the seven-sixteenths, chased three wide around most the far turn then moved to the four path, was driven five wide into the stretch and weakened. RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 6 1M Dirt CR: 82. Maiden Special Weight Purse 70000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD FOALED IN NEW YORK STATE AND APPROVED BY THE NEW YORK STATE-BRED REGISTRY. RACE.FOOTNOTES: REFUAH prompted the pace seven paths off the inside down the backstretch before tucking four wide through the turn, came under coaxing nearing the quarter pole and took over command swinging four to five wide into upper stretch, inched away under a drive to the eighth pole under a right handed crop, had the rider switch to the left hand and came outwards two paths herding INSPECTOR slightly near the sixteenth marker, dug in with that rival latching on and came out once more under a left handed swat bumping that foe before holding safe to the finish. INSPECTOR eight paths off the inside down the backstretch in aim of the front, tucked five wide through the turn coming under coaxing near the five-sixteenths, continued five wide into upper stretch, dug in under a drive rallying through the final furlong and getting herded a bit near the sixteenth marker while holding mostly to the path behind the leader rather than altering out, latched on to the outside of REFUAH just inside that station and had that rival come out once more getting bumped in the left shoulder and forcing the rider to pause and stand up in the irons in the final strides to the finish. METEORITE showed the way in hand four then three wide hounded by a trio, tucked three wide into the turn, came under coaxing at the three-eighths under challenge from RULE BREAKER to the inside, yielded the front with five-sixteenths to go and swung four wide into upper stretch loosely between foes, dug in under a drive angling out a furlong out and came again to secure the show honors in a good first effort. BATTLEOFLEXINGTON chased along the inside down the backstretch and then just off the inside through the turn patiently handled until set down spinning three wide into upper stretch, dug in under a drive offering up a mild kick to secure the last major share. RULE BREAKER just off the inside in aim of the front, advanced to press the pace through the turn taking narrow and brief command placed to coaxing at the five-sixteenths, got headed and spun just off the inside into upper stretch and weakened in the late stages. I'M JUST bobbled at the break, chased three to four wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, angled five to six wide into upper stretch and offered no response. WANNA WINNA six paths off the inside down the backstretch, tucked five wide through the turn coming under coaxing three furlongs from home, went seven wide into upper stretch and offered no rally. UNAFFECTED bobbled at the start, chased along the inside under a ride from midway on the turn, continued in the inside route into upper stretch and tired. There was a Stewards' Inquiry into the stretch run as well as a claim of foul by the rider of INSPECTOR alleging interference against REFUAH in the stretch. After review, it was deemed that REFUAH had interfered with INSPECTOR and therefore REFUAH was disqualified from victory and placed second for that interference before the race was declared official.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: UNION DOLLY was off a step slow, rounded the first turn in the two path, was well placed just off the pace, ranged up in the two path on the far turn, took the lead at the quarter-pole then kicked clear while set down in upper stretch, responded well in the final furlong and proved much the best under strong urging. FROM HELLO brushed with a rival at the start, went three wide on the first turn, settled towards the rear, traveled around the far turn in the two path, was roused late on that bend, came three wide into the stretch then moved further out, was caught behind a drifting foe coming to the furlong marker then altered course to the outside for room and finished with good courage to garner the place. UP HER SLEEVE went three wide on the first turn, settled off the pace, rounded the far turn in the two path, was given her cue inside the five-sixteenths, came three wide into the stretch then chased the winner, drifted out approaching the furlong marker and finished willingly for the show. LADY OF THOROTON had her saddle adjusted behind the gate, leaned out at the start then dropped well behind while sluggish early, went four wide on the first turn, was reserved at the rear, advanced three then four wide on the far turn, gained six wide into the stretch, held a reasonable striking position into the final furlong but lacked the needed response. BRISKY FROLIC went to the front, traveled around the first turn in the two path, showed the way down the backstretch, vied inside under extra left-rein guidance around the final turn, lost the advantage to the winner coming to the quarter-pole, moved out in upper stretch then came out further around the furlong marker and tired. GAME THEORY broke a bit awkwardly then brushed with an opponent, was taken in hand early then reserved while saving ground, came under encouragement late on the backstretch, lost her footing in the hindquarters at the three-eighths, moved closer along the rail passing the five-sixteenths, turned into upper stretch under a drive and lacked the needed response. R GIRL FAITH broke through the front of the gate prior to the start then was brought back around and reloaded, showed speed after breaking in front, was shut-off by BRISKY FROLIC just past the wire for the first time then steadied, stalked outside in the three path, was asked on the far turn and came up empty. BELLA PRINCIPESSA went four wide on the first turn, tracked the pace on the outside, came up empty while four then five wide on the far turn and faltered.
